719964f-a.title: Manhattan: Fulton Street - Church Street
719964f-a.text:
(1)
Fulton Sgreet, north side, west from but not including Church, to
and including West Streets. The 6 story buildings to the right center
(triangular cogoices) are Trinity Mission (No. 211) and St. Christopher
Chapel (No. 213).
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPROOUCTIONS.  August 6, 1930
(2)
The same view from Church Street. (Sixth Avenue ''El'' overhead,
demolished Spring 1939), showiag in the center of this block the
demolition of No's 201-3, the Lilly Suilding. In the foreground,
adjoining the corner is Hook and Ladder No. 10. The 2 story structure
at the corner (Nedicks) stands on the site of a former 5 story building
(No. 191 Fulton Street) which was demolished when Church Street was
widened during the construction period of the Municipal (Eighth Avenue)
subway. At the left appears Pier 14, occupied by the Fall River Line,
and the 1 story Glackner Suilding. The latter bears No's. 192 Greenwid:
Street and 227229 Fulton Street and stands at the N.W. corner.9bscuring
the lover portion of these is the Ninth Avenue ''E1''.
August 2, 1938
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
